storyInfo: Quercus's Arts can heal wounds, and grow plants. But would you believe that this time... an exuberantly lush tree has 'grown' an entire little boy?!

attributes.content: I'm starving...
attributes.name: Emaciated Child

attributes.content: (Sniffs) That smells amazing!
attributes.name: Emaciated Child

attributes.content: Hey, have you heard the news?
attributes.name: Dirt-Poor Peddler

attributes.content: The Druid's Treasure! Everyone's going mad about it!
attributes.name: Dirt-Poor Peddler

attributes.content: Can't be stuffed, can't be bothered, don't care.
attributes.name: Skint Peddler

attributes.content: If there is treasure, it goes to the upper crust. Not gonna make its way to us, is it?
attributes.name: Skint Peddler

attributes.content: Who says not?
attributes.name: Dirt-Poor Peddler

attributes.content: Oh, you think this is just our lot, eh? We deserve this?
attributes.name: Dirt-Poor Peddler

attributes.content: Look, forget that...
attributes.name: Skint Peddler

attributes.content: Someone's making off with your stuff.
attributes.name: Skint Peddler

attributes.content: (Treasure... my bruv's looking for that, right?)
attributes.name: Emaciated Child

attributes.content: (Okay, while the man's distracted...)
attributes.name: Emaciated Child

attributes.content: (Ow, hot!)
attributes.name: Emaciated Child

attributes.content: Hey!
attributes.name: Dirt-Poor Peddler

attributes.content: Trying to steal from me?!
attributes.name: Dirt-Poor Peddler

attributes.content: Krgh!
attributes.name: Emaciated Child

attributes.content: Bloody runt! Don't you dare muss up my stand!
attributes.name: Dirt-Poor Peddler

attributes.content: Get back here!
attributes.name: Dirt-Poor Peddler

attributes.content: How are your injuries?
attributes.name: Bitter Root

attributes.content: They're doing fine.
attributes.name: Quercus

attributes.content: No word from the Doctor still?
attributes.name: Quercus

attributes.content: Contact with them's been lost ever since they entered Londinium. All means of communication so far are kaput.
attributes.name: Bitter Root

attributes.content: What about your end?
attributes.name: Bitter Root

attributes.content: We've disseminated the news out.
attributes.name: Quercus

attributes.content: At the very least right now, no matter how many believe it, the Duke's people are letting us have the pretense of an investigation in order to station at the duchy's north border.
attributes.name: Quercus

attributes.content: If it all holds, we can come to the Doctor's rescue at any time.
attributes.name: Quercus

attributes.content: Hm... alright, good.
attributes.name: Bitter Root

attributes.content: For now, let's get these intel notes to the landship.
attributes.name: Quercus

attributes.content: The Doctor's group will be fine.
attributes.name: Quercus

attributes.content: They will.
attributes.name: Bitter Root

attributes.content: Right, the children at the refugee camp...
attributes.name: Bitter Root

attributes.content: Bring them here.
attributes.name: Quercus

attributes.content: It's... safer for them here.
attributes.name: Quercus

attributes.content: Susie wants you.
attributes.name: Bitter Root

attributes.content: I'll be off.
attributes.name: Bitter Root

attributes.content: Susie, didn't I tell you to get some proper rest first?
attributes.name: Quercus

attributes.content: I can cope here. I don't need help with anything, really.
attributes.name: Quercus

attributes.content: What's wrong? What has you so unhappy?
attributes.name: Quercus

attributes.content: The streets here, the city... everything's changed so much.
attributes.name: Goldenglow

attributes.content: I've never seen so many of the Guards out and about before.
attributes.name: Goldenglow

attributes.content: Everyone's rushing everywhere. We all look so tense.
attributes.name: Goldenglow

attributes.content: Nobody knows what the situation in Londinium is like right now.
attributes.name: Quercus

attributes.content: We have people escaping out here one after another, with nothing but scraps of testimonies and info contradicting info.
attributes.name: Quercus

attributes.content: It's become the source of panic and rumor in its own right.
attributes.name: Quercus

attributes.content: I know what's happening. You don't have to hide it from me, Quercus.
attributes.name: Goldenglow

attributes.content: Everyone's busy right now... I want to help too.
attributes.name: Goldenglow

attributes.content: Grani wouldn't even tell me about you and the refugees at first.
attributes.name: Goldenglow

attributes.content: I know... you're all looking out for me.
attributes.name: Goldenglow

attributes.content: You're a kind girl, Susie. That's why.
attributes.name: Quercus

attributes.content: Hm?
attributes.name: Goldenglow

attributes.content: Look, see the marks left on this leafâ€”bug-eaten, sun-bleached.
attributes.name: Quercus

attributes.content: Everything that's happening right now will be figured out.
attributes.name: Quercus

attributes.content: No matter if it's me, Grani, or anyone else who does it.
attributes.name: Quercus

attributes.content: No matter if it turns out well or not.
attributes.name: Quercus

attributes.content: And most people will forget it ever happened before long.
attributes.name: Quercus

attributes.content: But the ones who've been through it won't. Some marks are left forever.
attributes.name: Quercus

attributes.content: So...
attributes.name: Quercus

attributes.content: Listen, I'm not a child anymore!
attributes.name: Goldenglow

attributes.content: Quercus!
attributes.name: Goldenglow

attributes.content: Look, I made this bread myself, I learned how to do it aboard Rhodes Island.
attributes.name: Goldenglow

attributes.content: You always used to have to make me snacks, Quercus...
attributes.name: Goldenglow

attributes.content: So... I want to help you.
attributes.name: Goldenglow

attributes.content: Help everyone.
attributes.name: Goldenglow

attributes.content: I know.
attributes.name: Quercus

attributes.content: Oh, but still, it'll sting.
attributes.name: Quercus

attributes.content: Eh?
attributes.name: Goldenglow

attributes.content: Sting our little Susie, and Grani, and those children.
attributes.name: Quercus

attributes.content: You'll find nothing in the refugee camp but cries of distress, sighs of despair, and howls of longing.
attributes.name: Quercus

attributes.content: I've given everything I have to ward the haze of sickness from people, purely because they wouldn't resign themselves to death, because in their heart still laid cares.
attributes.name: Quercus

attributes.content: Some have calmly accepted the end of their life, and I've accompanied them in their final moments, in their tranquil return to the earth.
attributes.name: Quercus

attributes.content: But the endless spread of pestilence is drying and crumbling the soil beneath us, rendering it rough and unyielding.
attributes.name: Quercus

attributes.content: And that's why you want them to get the children out, and bring them here?
attributes.name: Goldenglow

attributes.content: Yes...
attributes.name: Quercus

attributes.content: All that takes place there is far too stifling for the newborn saplings.
attributes.name: Quercus

attributes.content: But that said...
attributes.name: Quercus

attributes.content: I've never doubted your ability nor your courage, Susie.
attributes.name: Quercus

attributes.content: So long as you're willing, you can come spend time with the children here from now on.
attributes.name: Quercus

attributes.content: Mm-hm!
attributes.name: Goldenglow

attributes.content: Also!
attributes.name: Goldenglow

attributes.content: I'm not a child anymore!
attributes.name: Goldenglow

attributes.content: And you're... so amazing, Quercus! You can use Arts to make withered plants regrow.
attributes.name: Goldenglow

attributes.content: Everything will get better.
attributes.name: Goldenglow

attributes.content: Arts are no panacea, you know.
attributes.name: Quercus

attributes.content: Take that frail, sickly sapling, for instance.
attributes.name: Quercus

attributes.content: The one in the corner.
attributes.name: Quercus

attributes.content: On an evening in early autumn, Quercus is quietly stood in the garden, listening in stillness.
The souls are mournful, their cry as clear as ever on the wind.
Well, meow...
attributes.name: Haze

attributes.content: I have to say, this is my first time seeing the Druid's Arts.
attributes.name: Haze

attributes.content: Wuh! When did you get here, Haze?
attributes.name: Goldenglow

attributes.content: Oh, I didn't. I've been here.
attributes.name: Haze

attributes.content: They say the Druid can hear what the trees make conversation over.
attributes.name: Haze

attributes.content: It's not conversation.
attributes.name: Quercus

attributes.content: It's the passing on of emotions, between souls, through the roots that connect life and the earth.
attributes.name: Quercus

attributes.content: Quercus softly chants an age-old incantation, Arts like stars falling down upon the mundane nature we inhabit, imparting themselves upon the earth.
In a bout of fierce tremors, a sapling ruptures through the ground, its finest form unfolding itself towards the vastness of the sky.
Atop the branches burst forth fresh buds, telling of the call that summons new life.
Wow!
attributes.name: Goldenglow

attributes.content: It just grew in an instant!
attributes.name: Goldenglow

attributes.content: Indeed.
attributes.name: Quercus

attributes.content: In an instant.
attributes.name: Quercus

attributes.content: Wait!
attributes.name: Goldenglow

attributes.content: Quercus! The... the tree!
attributes.name: Goldenglow

attributes.content: There's a child growing out of the tree!
attributes.name: Goldenglow

attributes.content: Once we find the Treasure, we want 60%.
attributes.name: Bent

attributes.content: 30% each for me and my little brother.
attributes.name: Bent

attributes.content: You want me to work, that's the price. No negotiations.
attributes.name: Bent

attributes.content: Look how greedy the legendary Bent's gotten.
attributes.name: Diminutive Mercenary

attributes.content: Getting too big for your britches, I bet.
attributes.name: Diminutive Mercenary

attributes.content: Alright. You want to go?
attributes.name: Bent

attributes.content: If you think we're actually scared of you, you can dream on.
attributes.name: Diminutive Mercenary

attributes.content: Guh!
attributes.name: Diminutive Mercenary

attributes.content: Got the guts to say that to me again?
attributes.name: Bent

attributes.content: 30%, alright, you said it, 30%.
attributes.name: Diminutive Mercenary

attributes.content: Each.
attributes.name: Bent

attributes.content: Oh, no, yeah, yeah!
attributes.name: Diminutive Mercenary

attributes.content: Now shove it.
attributes.name: Bent

attributes.content: Right...
attributes.name: Diminutive Mercenary

attributes.content: Wait. Any of you lot seen where my brother's about?
attributes.name: Bent

attributes.content: Er...
attributes.name: Diminutive Mercenary

attributes.content: Saw the kid earlier at one of those stands nearby.
attributes.name: Diminutive Mercenary

attributes.content: Carefree little bugger! I said for him not to run off!
attributes.name: Bent

attributes.content: Every single day with this! He drives me up the wall!
attributes.name: Bent

attributes.content: Hey!
attributes.name: Diminutive Mercenary

attributes.content: Still hiding?
attributes.name: Quercus

attributes.content: Little rascal.
attributes.name: Quercus

attributes.content: Oi!
attributes.name: Emaciated Child

attributes.content: Let me down!
attributes.name: Emaciated Child

attributes.content: Oh! I wonder who your family is.
attributes.name: Goldenglow

attributes.content: Let... Let me get you down now.
attributes.name: Goldenglow

attributes.content: Careful...
attributes.name: Goldenglow

attributes.content: Augh!
attributes.name: Goldenglow

attributes.content: Don't... Don't steal my bread!
attributes.name: Goldenglow

attributes.content: What's gotten into you?!
attributes.name: Goldenglow

attributes.content: (Muffled) I'm hungry! You've got loads of bread to spare!
attributes.name: Emaciated Child

attributes.content: Hey! Here, you!
attributes.name: Quercus

attributes.content: (This bread's delish...)
attributes.name: Emaciated Child

attributes.content: Wait, that's right!
attributes.name: Emaciated Child

attributes.content: You were just talking about the Druid, weren't you!
attributes.name: Emaciated Child

attributes.content: I've heard too! About the Druid's Treasure. My brother told me.
attributes.name: Emaciated Child

attributes.content: I bet you muckers know something!
attributes.name: Emaciated Child

attributes.content: Even if I did...
attributes.name: Quercus

attributes.content: Why would I tell you, hm?
attributes.name: Quercus

attributes.content: Because that's how it works.
attributes.name: Emaciated Child

attributes.content: Finders keepers, that's what my brother says!
attributes.name: Emaciated Child

attributes.content: Funny little boy.
attributes.name: Goldenglow

attributes.content: An unruly little kit.
attributes.name: Haze

attributes.content: If you don't tell me!
attributes.name: Emaciated Child

attributes.content: Then I'll tell my brother! I'll get him to ask you.
attributes.name: Emaciated Child

attributes.content: He's right tough!
attributes.name: Emaciated Child

attributes.content: Super! Super! Super tough!!!
attributes.name: Emaciated Child

attributes.content: *sigh*... I see.
attributes.name: Quercus

attributes.content: Well, one thing, young friend...
attributes.name: Quercus

attributes.content: After discovering our secret... do you think we're just going to let you go?
attributes.name: Quercus

attributes.content: Oi!
attributes.name: Emaciated Child

attributes.content: What's this about?! Stay away!!
attributes.name: Emaciated Child

attributes.content: I'm not scared of you, okay!
attributes.name: Emaciated Child

attributes.content: I'm mad tough too!
attributes.name: Emaciated Child

attributes.content: He's Infected?!
attributes.name: Goldenglow

attributes.content: I don't think he has an Arts Unit at all.
attributes.name: Goldenglow

attributes.content: Fool of a child!
attributes.name: Quercus

attributes.content: He thinks an ability for Arts means bragging rights?
attributes.name: Quercus

attributes.content: Heheh!
attributes.name: Emaciated Child

attributes.content: That's right! I can cast stuff!
attributes.name: Emaciated Child

attributes.content: I'm not as good as my brother, but you won't pick on me so easy!
attributes.name: Emaciated Child

attributes.content: You brat!
attributes.name: Quercus

attributes.content: You think you're so mighty, don't you?
attributes.name: Quercus

attributes.content: What are you up to?!
attributes.name: Emaciated Child

attributes.content: Hmph.
attributes.name: Quercus

attributes.content: Countless vines drop down from the tree above her, and the feeble child is fastened sturdily in place before he can even react.
He resembles a startled cub in the moment, gnashing as he struggles to flail.
Oi!
attributes.name: Emaciated Child

attributes.content: What are you doing?!
attributes.name: Emaciated Child

attributes.content: Spanking you.
attributes.name: Quercus

attributes.content: Disobedient child.
attributes.name: Quercus

attributes.content: Augh!
attributes.name: Emaciated Child

attributes.content: *whimper*...
attributes.name: Emaciated Child

attributes.content: I'll... I'll get my brother over here!
attributes.name: Emaciated Child

attributes.content: Do you think throwing around Arts randomly is going to make you fearsome?
attributes.name: Quercus

attributes.content: Without an Arts Unit, you'll be exacerbating your Oripathy every time.
attributes.name: Quercus

attributes.content: But my brother does it too!
attributes.name: Emaciated Child

attributes.content: His Arts...
attributes.name: Emaciated Child

attributes.content: Your brother?
attributes.name: Quercus

attributes.content: The harder you're infected... ugh...
attributes.name: Emaciated Child

attributes.content: That's what your brother taught you?
attributes.name: Quercus

attributes.content: Quercus, look at what he's dropped.
attributes.name: Goldenglow

attributes.content: Aren't these the medicines for Oripathy that you were getting in?
attributes.name: Goldenglow

attributes.content: Oi! That's my stuff!
attributes.name: Emaciated Child

attributes.content: Damn you! Give it back!
attributes.name: Emaciated Child

attributes.content: I found all that!
attributes.name: Emaciated Child

attributes.content: It was on a shelf inside and nobody was using it! Why can't I have it?
attributes.name: Emaciated Child

attributes.content: Stealing is one thing.
attributes.name: Quercus

attributes.content: But you're not to wantonly use your Arts ever again. If you want to stay alive, that is.
attributes.name: Quercus

attributes.content: Understand?
attributes.name: Quercus

attributes.content: ...I'm not scared!
attributes.name: Emaciated Child

attributes.content: My brother... My brother says this way nobody'll pick on me!
attributes.name: Emaciated Child

attributes.content: My brother's stronger than you! He'll come help me!
attributes.name: Emaciated Child

attributes.content: So your brother sent you here?
attributes.name: Quercus

attributes.content: For what?
attributes.name: Quercus

attributes.content: No!
attributes.name: Emaciated Child

attributes.content: I was waiting for my brother to come...
attributes.name: Emaciated Child

attributes.content: Then let me ask you a question.
attributes.name: Quercus

attributes.content: If your brother is as strong as you say...
attributes.name: Quercus

attributes.content: Why would he send you to do any of this?
attributes.name: Quercus

attributes.content: Are you sure your brother knows you're here?
attributes.name: Quercus

attributes.content: You didn't tell him you were heading out, did you?
attributes.name: Quercus

attributes.content: What if your brother never comes?
attributes.name: Quercus

attributes.content: What if... we leave you here? Will your brother really be able to find you?
attributes.name: Quercus

attributes.content: (Sobbing) I...
attributes.name: Emaciated Child

attributes.content: (Quercus, don't you think we've scared him a little too much?)
attributes.name: Goldenglow

attributes.content: (I mean, I know it's wrong to steal... child or not.)
attributes.name: Goldenglow

attributes.content: (I think our little Susie's just as much a child, then.)
attributes.name: Quercus

attributes.content: What if... we take you away from here?
attributes.name: Quercus

attributes.content: And you never see your brother again...
attributes.name: Quercus

attributes.content: No!
attributes.name: Emaciated Child

attributes.content: Don't... I...
attributes.name: Emaciated Child

attributes.content: I want to stay with my brother.
attributes.name: Emaciated Child

attributes.content: Then be truthful with me.
attributes.name: Quercus

attributes.content: Tell me why you stole this medicine, and why you're after the Druid's Treasure.
attributes.name: Quercus

attributes.content: Because my brother wanted it...
attributes.name: Emaciated Child

attributes.content: He's the one who looked after me ever since we left Londinium... He said there was treasure in Gododdin, and we could make loads and loads of money, and live happy days.
attributes.name: Emaciated Child

attributes.content: He's seriously, seriously strong! Nobody's ever been able to pick on us!
attributes.name: Emaciated Child

attributes.content: But he's been having worse and worse health, I can tell that... He's always using these medicines in secret.
attributes.name: Emaciated Child

attributes.content: This kind?
attributes.name: Quercus

attributes.content: I dunno. But it looks a lot like it.
attributes.name: Emaciated Child

attributes.content: I'm not a kid anymore.
attributes.name: Emaciated Child

attributes.content: I want to help my brother and all...
attributes.name: Emaciated Child

attributes.content: If I can find the treasure, and some medicine!
attributes.name: Emaciated Child

attributes.content: Then that'll make my brother super duper happy!
attributes.name: Emaciated Child

attributes.content: So...
attributes.name: Emaciated Child

attributes.content: Please, Miss.
attributes.name: Emaciated Child

attributes.content: Can you...
attributes.name: Emaciated Child

attributes.content: I understand.
attributes.name: Quercus

attributes.content: But still, I can't tell you right this moment.
attributes.name: Quercus

attributes.content: Oh...
attributes.name: Emaciated Child

attributes.content: Then... Then what do I have to do, before you tell me?
attributes.name: Emaciated Child

attributes.content: I'm just here to check if you have everything all in place and sorted.
attributes.name: Bitter Root

attributes.content: I'll have Grani accompany the kids over.
attributes.name: Bitter Root

attributes.content: Everything's ready.
attributes.name: Quercus

attributes.content: That kid in the garden...
attributes.name: Bitter Root

attributes.content: You have some amazing patience.
attributes.name: Bitter Root

attributes.content: I'm only a doctor.
attributes.name: Quercus

attributes.content: I don't accede to every whim. I'm no fairy godmother.
attributes.name: Quercus

attributes.content: *sigh*... He's had a hard lot in life.
attributes.name: Bitter Root

attributes.content: We don't even know how his brother is.
attributes.name: Bitter Root

attributes.content: That's why I sent Susie back for now.
attributes.name: Quercus

attributes.content: She's too kind...
attributes.name: Quercus

attributes.content: And as you meet each refugee in the camp, and every child that's sent here... you find each and every story tugs at your heart, doesn't it?
attributes.name: Quercus

attributes.content: That's why little Susie's the one I'm more worried for, really.
attributes.name: Quercus

attributes.content: *sigh*...
attributes.name: Bitter Root

attributes.content: And how are you going to explain the Druid's Treasure to him, then?
attributes.name: Bitter Root

attributes.content: All it is is the cover we operate under. You know that.
attributes.name: Bitter Root

attributes.content: Not to mention we've still not heard a peep from the Doctor's end. We can't expose this.
attributes.name: Bitter Root

attributes.content: We have to prioritize Rhodes Island and our mission.
attributes.name: Bitter Root

attributes.content: So...
attributes.name: Quercus

attributes.content: We give him a false goal, one that can never be achieved?
attributes.name: Quercus

attributes.content: Make him chase fruitlessly, cluelessly, for the rest of his days?
attributes.name: Quercus

attributes.content: A sacrifice?
attributes.name: Quercus

attributes.content: What do you mean?
attributes.name: Bitter Root

attributes.content: A sacrifice?
attributes.name: Bitter Root

attributes.content: I just feel...
attributes.name: Quercus

attributes.content: It's not how Rhodes Island would do things.
attributes.name: Quercus

attributes.content: We can't just absolve ourselves of our actions like that.
attributes.name: Quercus

attributes.content: What are you going to do?!
attributes.name: Bitter Root

attributes.content: Quercus, stop right there!
attributes.name: Bitter Root

attributes.content: Explain.
attributes.name: Bitter Root

attributes.content: Don't worry. I won't do anything to hurt Rhodes Island.
attributes.name: Quercus

attributes.content: Oi!
attributes.name: Bent

attributes.content: Question for you. Seen a kid about this tall?
attributes.name: Bent

attributes.content: The hell do you think you're doing?!
attributes.name: Dirt-Poor Peddler

attributes.content: Bloody hell! It was that little bastard just now! Your brother, I reckon, you look like two peas in a pod!
attributes.name: Dirt-Poor Peddler

attributes.content: Here I was narked I'd have no one to pay damages...
attributes.name: Dirt-Poor Peddler

attributes.content: You...
attributes.name: Dirt-Poor Peddler

attributes.content: Where is he?!
attributes.name: Bent

attributes.content: The weak, frail figure of a child busies about the garden.
Miss Quercus! I watered all the trees in the garden!
attributes.name: Emaciated Child

attributes.content: (It's only a momentary drive.)
attributes.name: Quercus

attributes.content: I swept the path over there all nice and clean too!
attributes.name: Emaciated Child

attributes.content: (He may well be worn out any second now.)
attributes.name: Quercus

attributes.content: What else do I need to do?
attributes.name: Emaciated Child

attributes.content: (He throws himself dim-wittedly at everything without even knowing what this treasure is.)
attributes.name: Quercus

attributes.content: Do you know why I'm having you do these things?
attributes.name: Quercus

attributes.content: Nope.
attributes.name: Emaciated Child

attributes.content: That one mister says it's because I've done bad things.
attributes.name: Emaciated Child

attributes.content: And have you?
attributes.name: Quercus

attributes.content: I don't know...
attributes.name: Emaciated Child

attributes.content: My brother's always done it. He says other people owe us all this stuff.
attributes.name: Emaciated Child

attributes.content: It's stuff we're meant to have.
attributes.name: Emaciated Child

attributes.content: (The branches that rot are bade to be pruned.)
attributes.name: Quercus

attributes.content: (The trunks that are gnawed are bade to be sawed.)
attributes.name: Quercus

attributes.content: Let me put it this way, then.
attributes.name: Quercus

attributes.content: You did something that ended with you being caught, and you put your brother through the hassle of saving you.
attributes.name: Quercus

attributes.content: Was that bad of you?
attributes.name: Quercus

attributes.content: ...Mm-hm.
attributes.name: Emaciated Child

attributes.content: So if your brother gets hurt while saving you...
attributes.name: Quercus

attributes.content: Possibly... even worse.
attributes.name: Quercus

attributes.content: Is that bad of you then?
attributes.name: Quercus

attributes.content: It is!
attributes.name: Emaciated Child

attributes.content: Just as you cherish your brother, others have their own things, and their own people they cherish.
attributes.name: Quercus

attributes.content: If you take things as you see fit, then you'll make others angry, and get your brother into trouble in the end.
attributes.name: Quercus

attributes.content: Understand?
attributes.name: Quercus

attributes.content: Mm-hm...
attributes.name: Emaciated Child

attributes.content: I understand.
attributes.name: Emaciated Child

attributes.content: I won't do bad things anymore.
attributes.name: Emaciated Child

attributes.content: (But who can say what form the treetop takes in this moment?)
attributes.name: Quercus

attributes.content: (May life everlast.)
attributes.name: Quercus

attributes.content: Here?
attributes.name: Bent

attributes.content: A... Around here...
attributes.name: Dirt-Poor Peddler

attributes.content: I chased him up to around here, and then, and then I lost him.
attributes.name: Dirt-Poor Peddler

attributes.content: Guh!
attributes.name: Dirt-Poor Peddler

attributes.content: Now shove it.
attributes.name: Bent

attributes.content: Joe?
attributes.name: Bent

attributes.content: Are you there?
attributes.name: Bent

attributes.content: Bent!
attributes.name: Emaciated Child

attributes.content: You're here?!
attributes.name: Emaciated Child

attributes.content: Um!!
attributes.name: Emaciated Child

attributes.content: I said for you not to run off!
attributes.name: Bent

attributes.content: I went through hell to scarper out with you! Every step of the way, you know how hard it's been?!
attributes.name: Bent

attributes.content: Don't you hang your head! I'm talking to you!
attributes.name: Bent

attributes.content: (Need me to help that kid out?)
attributes.name: Bitter Root

attributes.content: (We can't leave him with someone like this, can we?)
attributes.name: Bitter Root

attributes.content: Who're you?
attributes.name: Bent

attributes.content: Don't get in the way! Move it!
attributes.name: Bent

attributes.content: You're this child's elder brother?
attributes.name: Quercus

attributes.content: And what's your business?
attributes.name: Bent

attributes.content: 'Joe.' Is that your name?
attributes.name: Quercus

attributes.content: Right, with me. We're going home.
attributes.name: Bent

attributes.content: I'm not going.
attributes.name: Joe

attributes.content: Can you just listen for once?!
attributes.name: Bent

attributes.content: You're stressing me out like this! Me, Mum and Dad, who do you think we've done everything for?
attributes.name: Bent

attributes.content: I'm not going.
attributes.name: Joe

attributes.content: You think I'm no use anymore, don't you? You think I can't provide for you, is it?!
attributes.name: Bent

attributes.content: Think you've outgrown the nest, don't need me looking after you?
attributes.name: Bent

attributes.content: Eh?!
attributes.name: Bent

attributes.content: Let me go!
attributes.name: Bent

attributes.content: This is not for an outsider like you to butt in. It's family business.
attributes.name: Bent

attributes.content: (Bitter Root.)
attributes.name: Quercus

attributes.content: (Take the child aside.)
attributes.name: Quercus

attributes.content: What are you doing?
attributes.name: Bent

attributes.content: Argh!
attributes.name: Bent

attributes.content: Urgh!
attributes.name: Bent

attributes.content: You let me go!
attributes.name: Bent

attributes.content: Are we clear? I could easily dispose of you right now.
attributes.name: Quercus

attributes.content: And even your little brother.
attributes.name: Quercus

attributes.content: All because of how reckless you've been.
attributes.name: Quercus

attributes.content: You make me angry.
attributes.name: Quercus

attributes.content: You!!
attributes.name: Bent

attributes.content: Argh!
attributes.name: Bent

attributes.content: Quiet!
attributes.name: Quercus

attributes.content: Will you listen properly now?
attributes.name: Quercus

attributes.content: Mmrgh...
attributes.name: Bent

attributes.content: I can put up with your insolence.
attributes.name: Quercus

attributes.content: It's not as if I don't respect all you've done for the child.
attributes.name: Quercus

attributes.content: I imagine you know the state of your infection all too well. Do you want to see the child end up the same way?
attributes.name: Quercus

attributes.content: Was it you who taught him to use Arts to defend himself?
attributes.name: Quercus

attributes.content: I had no other choice. It's the only thing they fear.
attributes.name: Bent

attributes.content: And do you see fear in me?
attributes.name: Quercus

attributes.content: What if I killed the two of you right here and now?
attributes.name: Quercus

attributes.content: You wouldn't dare!
attributes.name: Bent

attributes.content: I'd take you with me!
attributes.name: Bent

attributes.content: So you don't intend on surviving?
attributes.name: Quercus

attributes.content: What about your brother, then?
attributes.name: Quercus

attributes.content: What is it you want?
attributes.name: Bent

attributes.content: It's a secret between me and him.
attributes.name: Quercus

attributes.content: I won't allow you to take him until he fulfils his agreement with me.
attributes.name: Quercus

attributes.content: You can go back to your current dwellings and wait for him.
attributes.name: Quercus

attributes.content: Of course, my people can find you at any time.
attributes.name: Quercus

attributes.content: Or you could go to the refugee camp on the east end. They'll offer you help there.
attributes.name: Quercus

attributes.content: Is my point clear?
attributes.name: Quercus

attributes.content: See?
attributes.name: Quercus

attributes.content: It turns out we can have a proper conversation.
attributes.name: Quercus

attributes.content: Argh!
attributes.name: Bitter Root

attributes.content: Hey! Watch it, boy!
attributes.name: Bitter Root

attributes.content: You're biting the hand that feeds you.
attributes.name: Bitter Root

attributes.content: Miss Quercus!
attributes.name: Joe

attributes.content: Let my brother go!
attributes.name: Joe

attributes.content: He's a good person!
attributes.name: Joe

attributes.content: He's the best in all the land!
attributes.name: Joe

attributes.content: So I won't let you hurt him!
attributes.name: Joe

attributes.content: *sigh*...
attributes.name: Quercus

attributes.content: How am I the villain now?
attributes.name: Quercus

attributes.content: The boy's got real strength when it counts...
attributes.name: Bitter Root

attributes.content: Joe, do you remember what you asked me about earlier on?
attributes.name: Quercus

attributes.content: Be good and come with me now, and I'll tell you all you want to know.
attributes.name: Quercus

attributes.content: And I promise I won't hurt your brother, okay?
attributes.name: Quercus

attributes.content: Okay!
attributes.name: Joe

attributes.content: Now, do you think we're bad people?
attributes.name: Quercus

attributes.content: If you and that mister pick on my brother, then yeah.
attributes.name: Joe

attributes.content: So why didn't you use Arts just now to attack that mister, and save your brother?
attributes.name: Quercus

attributes.content: Because you said using Arts would make the infection worse.
attributes.name: Joe

attributes.content: It's bad and it'll make my brother worry.
attributes.name: Joe

attributes.content: So if I told you that you had to exchange your brother for the treasure, you wouldn't agree, would you?
attributes.name: Quercus

attributes.content: I wouldn't do it, even if it was for treasure.
attributes.name: Joe

attributes.content: I would never... never ever!
attributes.name: Joe

attributes.content: (A life yet to bud grows with wild abandon.)
attributes.name: Quercus

attributes.content: Congratulations.
attributes.name: Quercus

attributes.content: You've passed the test.
attributes.name: Quercus

attributes.content: What?!
attributes.name: Joe

attributes.content: Only those who become Druids are qualified to find the Druid's Treasure.
attributes.name: Quercus

attributes.content: And you've successfully passed the first test.
attributes.name: Quercus

attributes.content: Eh?
attributes.name: Joe

attributes.content: Becoming a Druid?
attributes.name: Joe

attributes.content: Indeed.
attributes.name: Quercus

attributes.content: Come with me.
attributes.name: Quercus

attributes.content: What's this place?
attributes.name: Joe

attributes.content: This... is a place once holy to the Druids.
attributes.name: Quercus

attributes.content: Only, the vast amount of time has made the legends hazy.
attributes.name: Quercus

attributes.content: Here, age after age of tutor imparted the knowledge and the precepts upon the next generation.
attributes.name: Quercus

attributes.content: Until the Druids began to die out, ever so gradually, in Victoria's history.
attributes.name: Quercus

attributes.content: Joe, go and kneel upon the altar there.
attributes.name: Quercus

attributes.content: Mm-hm.
attributes.name: Joe

attributes.content: Quercus snaps off cane from a tree, and flogs Joe across his back with force.
The searing pain forces him to bend over, upon which he immediately, stubbornly rights himself again.
Joe, young stray that you are.
attributes.name: Quercus

attributes.content: May the age-old faith be carved hardily into your heart. For all tribulation the future brings, shall your way forward never stray.
attributes.name: Quercus

attributes.content: Quercus takes a berry from the bush, and with her thumb, draws a line of vivid red over the forehead of Joe.
May the roots of the earth ever be bound with you. For however far you are separated from home, shall you never be lost nor hesitant.
attributes.name: Quercus

attributes.content: The branches that rot are bade to be pruned.
attributes.name: Quercus

attributes.content: The trunks that are gnawed are bade to be sawed.
attributes.name: Quercus

attributes.content: May life everlast.
attributes.name: Quercus

attributes.content: Joe, I ask if you are willing to swear upon the ancient precepts, and become a true Druid.
attributes.name: Quercus

attributes.content: I am.
attributes.name: Joe

attributes.content: Rise. From today forth, you are a Druid!
attributes.name: Quercus

attributes.content: I'm a Druid now?
attributes.name: Joe

attributes.content: Mm. From here on, you must rely on yourself to seek the treasure of legend.
attributes.name: Quercus

attributes.content: Have you found it then, Miss Quercus?
attributes.name: Joe

attributes.content: Not yet, no. I think... you'll find it before I do, perhaps.
attributes.name: Quercus

attributes.content: Really?
attributes.name: Joe

attributes.content: Really.
attributes.name: Quercus

attributes.content: But you must keep it secret.
attributes.name: Quercus

attributes.content: For if you catch the eye of some very, very bad people, then they'll catch you, hurt you, and even hurt your brother.
attributes.name: Quercus

attributes.content: Understand?
attributes.name: Quercus

attributes.content: Mm-hm...
attributes.name: Joe

attributes.content: That's a bad thing. I won't do it.
attributes.name: Joe

attributes.content: So... can I tell my brother?
attributes.name: Joe

attributes.content: What, you mean...
attributes.name: Quercus

attributes.content: You wouldn't want to surprise him with something nice?
attributes.name: Quercus

attributes.content: See what I mean?
attributes.name: Quercus

attributes.content: Oh...
attributes.name: Joe

attributes.content: Okay!
attributes.name: Joe

attributes.content: You're not honestly counting on a little kid to keep a secret, right?
attributes.name: Bitter Root

attributes.content: How much danger will you bring on yourself if word of this gets out?
attributes.name: Bitter Root

attributes.content: Not too many know of my relations with Rhodes Island.
attributes.name: Quercus

attributes.content: But you've been meeting me often lately. Some people have started to notice already.
attributes.name: Quercus

attributes.content: So if necessary, we can have a falling-out take place between us.
attributes.name: Quercus

attributes.content: Would you rather I bring the danger upon Rhodes Island and the Doctor, then?
attributes.name: Quercus

attributes.content: Hence why I make this choice.
attributes.name: Quercus

attributes.content: Not to mention...
attributes.name: Quercus

attributes.content: The Druids' legends, the stories of and about life, have been forgotten for far too long.
attributes.name: Quercus

attributes.content: They need to be told anew by people.
attributes.name: Quercus

attributes.content: You know that kid's never going to find any so-called treasure.
attributes.name: Bitter Root

attributes.content: Who told you there was no treasure?
attributes.name: Quercus

attributes.content: You did?
attributes.name: Bitter Root

attributes.content: Because you're not a Druid, see.
attributes.name: Quercus

attributes.content: Only Druids will find the Druid's Treasure.
attributes.name: Quercus

attributes.content: Eh?
attributes.name: Bitter Root

attributes.content: What?
attributes.name: Bitter Root

attributes.content: So that little ritual you did before with the incantation or whatever, that was all real?
attributes.name: Bitter Root

attributes.content: Oh... well, not that, I made that up.
attributes.name: Quercus

attributes.content: I just haven't found any of the historical files or data yet, that's the bare minimum of it.
attributes.name: Quercus

attributes.content: You weren't really taken in by that, were you?
attributes.name: Quercus
